summary: An ordinance accepting deeds from E. R. Murphy and wife Carrie, to The City of Seattle, executed on the 17th day of June, 1924; from Otto Lorbeer and Martha Lorbeer, his wife, to The City of Seattle, executed on the 19th day of June, 1924; and from Annie Murphy to The City of Seattle, executed on the 17th day of June, 1924; and laying off West Austin Street.
